  "prompt": "How do I uninstall Modified apk by Lucky Patcher (I can only deactivate it)?",
  "response": "Uninstalling a modified APK created with Lucky Patcher can sometimes be tricky because Android may not recognize it as a standard app. Here's how you can remove it:\n\n---\n\n### **Method 1: Using a File Manager**\n1. **Find the Modified APK**:\n   - Open a file manager app (like **ES File Explorer** or **Solid Explorer**).\n   - Navigate to the folder where the modified APK is installed (often in `/data/app/` or `/sdcard/`).\n\n2. **Delete the APK**:\n   - Locate the APK file associated with the modified app.\n   - Long-press the file and select **Delete**.\n\n3. **Clear App Data (Optional)**:\n   - Go to **Settings > Apps** (or **Apps & Notifications**).\n   - Find the modified app and clear its data before uninstalling.\n\n4. **Uninstall the App**:\n   - Still in **Settings > Apps**, select the modified app and tap **Uninstall**.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 2: Via Lucky Patcher**\n1. Open **Lucky Patcher**.\n2. Go to the **Tools** tab.\n3. Select **Remove Patch/Uninstall**.\n4. Find the modified app in the list and select **Uninstall**.\n\n---\n\n### **Method 3: Using ADB (Advanced)**\nIf the app cannot be uninstalled through normal methods, you can use ADB (Android Debug Bridge) to remove it:\n1. Enable **Developer Options** on your device (go to **Settings > About Phone > Tap Build Number 7 times**).\n2. Enable **USB Debugging** in **Developer Options**.\n3. Connect your device to a computer with ADB installed.\n4. Open a command prompt or terminal and type:\n   ```\n   adb shell pm uninstall -k --user 0 <package_name>\n   ```\n   Replace `<package_name>` with the package name of the modified app (e.g., `com.example.app`).\n\n---\n\n### **Method 4: Factory Reset (Last Resort)**\nIf none of the above methods work, you may need to perform a **factory reset** on your device. Be sure to back up your data first, as this will erase everything on your device.\n\n---\n\n### **Note**:\n- **Lucky Patcher** and modified APKs can sometimes cause issues with your device or apps. Always be cautious when using such tools.\n- Ensure you are uninstalling the correct app to avoid removing essential system apps.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
